d4538aa6-dd7f-407a-8d42-be2739baadfb.0274be60-1b32-48af-8ba4-00dfcd81fe0a.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
d4538aa6-dd7f-407a-8d42-be2739baadfb.0656ada6-dacc-4fe4-8603-d84b959ad09d.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

d4538aa6-dd7f-407a-8d42-be2739baadfb.28979b86-e282-41bf-8a2f-3000674d45c8.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null. 
Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
d4538aa6-dd7f-407a-8d42-be2739baadfb.3a5f3464-8084-44f2-99ff-023a14b30964.description=
Scans for a specified HTML tag and returns the content found between that tag and its closing tag. 

Inputs\:
    html - The HTML to parse. This is the actual HTML, not the path to an HMTL file.
    occurrenceNumber - Specifies which flagged section to return. A value of '1' indicates the first section, '2' the second and so on. A value of '0' indicates the return of the entire document.
    startTag - The HTML tag to parse on. 
Example\: 
    endTag - The closing HTML tag to parse on.
Example\: 


Results\:
    Result - The information contained between the  and . 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully. The html does not have enough occurrences of tag.

Note\:
This operation adds to the context two variables  and . These two variables contain the names and the values of the HTML attributes present in the tag found by the operation. For example, if the tag that is found is something like 
     ... 

the two variables are\:
    htmlParamNames\: dir,align
    htmlParamValues\: rtl,center
In a flow containing an "HTML Parser" step, these two variables can be fetched from the context and used in subsequent steps.

Example\:
If the tag is 'table', everything between  and 
 is returned. The function does support nested tables\:

foo


bar




moo


The inner table ('bar') cannot be retrieved. 
'foo' or 'moo' can be retrieved. If 'foo' is retrieved, it contains the 'bar' sub-table.

d4538aa6-dd7f-407a-8d42-be2739baadfb.f4e31da6-48b4-4e34-b8c1-1eb6a0cabc1f.description=
Extracts the name-value pair of an  tag from a list containing the HTML parameter names and values of the form's  tag.

Inputs\: 
    htmlParamNames - The parameter names parsed from the form  tag. 
    htmlParamValues - The parameter values parsed from the form  tag. 

Results\:
    returnCode - This is the primary output. A code used to determine the operation response, specifying whether the operation is successful or not.
    names - The name field of the  tag.
    values - The value field of the  tag.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully. Either the  and  did not contain a name-value pair, or the numbers of elements provided in the  and  list inputs are different.

Example\: 
If the HTML  tag is , enter the value of  as "type,name,value" and the value of  as "text,user,John".
The operation output is\: 
    names\: user
    values\: John
